title: Root to Rise: Grounding oneself through Aromatherapy and Flow [Sepulveda Garden Compost Hub]
description:
Align with the rhythms of nature and reconnect with your inner foundation in a grounding immersion of movement and aromatherapy.  Root to Rise is a restorative movement and aromatherapy workshop designed to explore how rooting into our own well-being allows us to show up more fully for our communities. Just as trees root deeply before they rise, we too must ground ourselves to grow. Through gentle yoga and aromatic oils, we’ll tune into the wisdom of nature and the power of collective healing. With each breath, we invite balance; with each movement, we create space to rise.

About LA Compost's Grounded Wellness Program:
LA Compost's Grounded Wellness Workshop Series provides free, hands-on workshops at Community Compost Hubs in Los Angeles, focusing on wellness through soil health, personal well-being, and community connection. Each workshop celebrates the gifts of the earth while fostering meaningful connections with nature and neighbors. Interactive experiences led by local instructors highlight the connections between healthy soil, a thriving planet, and our well-being.

For more info, visit lacompost.org/groundedwellness.

title: Gatherings: Impacts of Medicaid & Healthcare Funding Cuts on Mat-Su Healthcare
description:
# **Gatherings: Potluck & Community Conversation on Healthcare in the Mat-Su**

Join us for *Gatherings*, our community potluck and conversation series—this time with a special **watch party and discussion** on one of the most urgent issues facing our community: cuts to Medicaid and healthcare funding in Alaska.

We'll begin with a **free hot dog dinner** — we’re providing the hot dogs and buns! We’re asking attendees to help round out the meal by bringing toppings (like chopped onions or tomatoes) or a side dish (such as potato salad, chips, or baked beans). It’s a potluck in the truest sense—sharing food and ideas.

After we eat, we’ll watch a **recorded webinar**:  
### *Medicaid 101: What It Is, What It’s Not, and What Potential Significant Cuts Could Mean for Alaskans*

This powerful webinar features **Alaskan healthcare experts** and is moderated by the Mat-Su’s own **Elizabeth Ripley**, former Executive Director of the Mat-Su Health Foundation. You’ll also hear from **Rose O’Hara-Jolley (they/them)**, State Director for Planned Parenthood Alliance Advocates, who will provide essential insight into how these cuts could impact reproductive healthcare in our state.

We’ll open the floor for discussion, reflection, and next steps. You don’t need to be an expert to attend—just someone who cares about the health and future of our community.

**Bring a dish, bring a friend, and bring your voice.**  
Let’s stand together for healthcare in the Mat-Su and across Alaska.

### **Why It Matters**
Medicaid and healthcare funding are a lifeline for many in our community. Changes and cuts to these programs can feel personal – from longer wait times at the clinic, to neighbors struggling to afford care. *Gatherings* is our chance to come together in the face of these challenges. By sharing stories and information, we can support one another and brainstorm ways to cope and advocate for our community’s health. The issue is important, but **you don’t need to be an expert** to attend – just come with an open mind and caring heart.

### **You’re Invited**
This event is **open to everyone**. Feel free to **bring a friend or family member** along – the more voices in the room, the stronger our community. Even if you can’t bring a dish, please **come anyway**; there will be plenty to share.  

We believe that a **shared meal and honest conversation** can spark understanding and action. So bring a dish, bring a friend, and **join the conversation**!

We look forward to seeing you at *Gatherings* for an evening of learning, sharing, and community spirit.

**Join the Rise for Freedom Coalition for a series of live online trainings intended for in-person groups nationwide for 6-8 weeks.** The goal of the training series is to bring people together, grow & strengthen their local networks, and get ready to mobilize to demand democracy in this new challenging environment.

*   Training content will be presented live and breakouts will take place in-person in people’s living rooms and other activist organized spaces. 
    
*   Follow up asks deemed the most important to the moment will be shared at the end of trainings as appropriate.
    
*   Training is a flexible tool that can help build for specific events as well as build existing and new local groups of people who can take action together.
    

#### **Why Trainings?**

Trainings are critical for our movement because they:

*   **Engage and recruit** more people into the freedom and democracy movement
    
*   **Educate** and onboard new activists
    
*   **Energize** large numbers of people for mobilizing and create space for local organizing and planning
    
*   **Elevate:** train higher skill activists and new and younger movement  leadership
    

**Who is Rise for Democracy For?**

This training is for people who love our country and understand the threat of autocracy before us, and want to do something about it. If you're moderate politically - this is your place! You are welcome and important here. If you're a pro-democracy conservative - this is your place! You are welcome and important in these trainings. If you’re progressive, this training is for you. 

#### **All Trainings Will Include:**

*   Music
    
*   An icebreaker
    
*   Asks for local leaders to help you prepare for action
    
*   Outreach mini training and goal setting (e.g. text 5 ppl and get 1 commit to come to your next meeting, recruit one neighbor to attend etc)
    
*   One digital hygiene tip 
    
*   One core 1.5- 2 hour training module
    
*   Breakouts for in-person and online for folks who are alone, to plan and participate in activities
    

Training calls will _not_ include lengthy one way communications about the ongoing attacks on democracy and communities. That’s a space other orgs and collaboratives we believe can and will fill.

#### **Rise for Freedom Training Timeline**

*   **Thurs. March 27 – First In-Person Meetings & Onboarding for New Folks:** Program Orientation & Context Setting, Outreach & Digital Hygiene
    
*   **Thurs. April 3 –** How did we get here? Intro to organizing under creeping autocracy
    
*   **Thurs. April 10 –** Building to a critical mass locally (outreach)
    
*   **Thurs. April 17 –** How to Talk to People You Might Disagree With
    
*   **Thurs. April 24 –** Harnessing Our Power to End Political Violence and Repression
    
*   **Thurs. May 1 – BREAK (no training): Find or host a May Day mobilization:** [**may1dayofaction.org**](https://www.may1dayofaction.org/) **(immigration focused) or** [**maydaystrong.org**](https://maydaystrong.org/) **(union led)**
    
*   **Thurs. May 8 –** De-escalation & Advanced Strategic organizing skills
    
*   **Thurs. May 15 –** Mutual Aid & Structures for Stronger Local Organizing
    
*   **Thurs. May 22 –** Advanced Organizing Skills: Choosing your Tactics 
    
*   **Thurs. May 29** **–** Digital Hygiene for Activists
    
*   **Thurs. June 5** **–** Media Storytelling with a Focus on Broadcast and Social Media

title: Stamford Immigration Forum: Extend HUSKY & Protect Immigrants
description:
The attacks on our immigrant communities are escalating, but so is our determination to build people power! We’re seeing ICE kidnap people from our communities and disappear them to foreign prisons. Our CT Elected officials MUST stand on the right side of history.

Join us for a Community Immigration Forum in Stamford where we will hear from community members, elected officials, and allies on why protecting and extending HUSKY for Immigrants and passing the TRUST Act are key actions CT can take to protect immigrant communities, and how YOU can take immediate action in support of our immigrant community members.

🔵 When: Sunday, May 18th, 2:00pm to 4:00pm

🔵 Where: Unitarian Universalist Congregation | 20 Forest St, Stamford, CT 06901


Connecticut has made remarkable progress - In the last 4 years, the HUSKY for Immigrants coalition successfully expanded HUSKY coverage to over 19,000 undocumented children ages 0-15 and to undocumented pregnant people. We cannot let CT move backward.
 
**What are we fighting for?**

🗣️ Protect our progress and maintain HUSKY Medicaid coverage for undocumented children age 15 and under, and pregnant individuals.

🗣️ Raise the age for HUSKY eligibility up to age 26, for all income-eligible residents regardless of immigration status.

🗣️ Pass the TRUST Act (HB 7212), a bill that would protect our CT immigrant community from ICE abductions and protect CT local resources from being used to further mass deportations.

Stamford is and must continue to be a welcoming place for all our residents, where all of us, regardless of race, religion, sexual orientation, and immigration status, can feel safe!!

*Sponsoring organizations of the event include: the HUSKY 4 Immigrants Coalition, TRUST Act, NOW Coalition, 32BJ, Social Justice Committee of the UU Congregation in Stamford, UPSS - United Parents For Students Sucesss, Interfaith Council of Southwestern Connecticut, Stamford Indivisible, Comunidades Sin Frontreras, UPASS, Nosotr@s, and other local organizations. *

title: Fair School Funding Virtual Town Hall - Cleveland
description:
Join us for a virtual town hall where we'll fight for the schools all our kids deserve!

We believe that every child, regardless of their race or family's income, has the right to a quality education that opens doors to their dreams. But for too long, Ohio's school funding system has fallen short, creating an uneven playing field where some kids get more opportunities than others.

This isn't just about numbers; it's about justice. When we underfund our schools, it disproportionately harms Black and brown students, as well as children in low-income communities, and children with special needs. It denies them the resources they need to thrive, perpetuating cycles of inequality.

At this town hall, we will:

-Learn how state funding decisions are impacting our schools

-Expose how the current system and the Ohio House’s version of the state budget perpetuate racial and economic disparities

-Share our stories

-Take immediate actions to advocate for our schools

-Organize to build a powerful movement of parents, students, teachers, and community members who won't settle for anything less than equity

It's time to rewrite the narrative. Let's demand that our lawmakers fully fund the Fair School Funding Plan, a solution that takes into account the actual needs of each district. Our kids are counting on us to build a future where their zip code doesn't determine their destiny.

The chaos fueled by Trump’s authoritarian ambitions and Musk’s reckless influence can make the future feel bleak. But we’re not powerless and the numbers show just how close we are to taking back control.
